01312]]<ref name=sb1112>{{soccerbase season|31018|2011|accessdate=19 November 2014}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|36||0||6||2||4||0||colspan=2|\u2014||46||2\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Liverpool F.C. season|2012\u201313]]<ref name=sb1213>{{soccerbase season|31018|2012|accessdate=19 November 2014}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|29||3||2||0||2||0||12{{efn|name=UEL}}||2||45||5\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!65||3||8||2||6||0||12||2||91||7\n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]]\n|[[2013\u201314 West Ham United F.C. season|2013\u201314]]<ref name=sb1314>{{soccerbase season|31018|2013|accessdate=19 November 2014}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|32||1||1||0||4||0||colspan=2|\u2014||37||1\n|-\n|[[2014\u201315 West Ham United F.C. season|2014\u201315]]<ref name=sb1415>{{soccerbase season|31018|2014|accessdate=21 September 2016}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|37||6||4||0||1||0||colspan=2|\u2014||42||6\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!69||7||5||0||5||0||colspan=2|\u2014||79||7\n|-\n|rowspan=5|Middlesbrough\n|[[2015\u201316 Middlesbrough F.C. season|2015\u201316]]<ref name=sb1516>{{soccerbase season|31018|2015|accessdate=21 September 2016}}</ref>\n|[[EFL Championship|Championship]]\n|45||3||0||0||4||0||colspan=2|\u2014||49||3\n|-\n|[[2016\u201317 Middlesbrough F.C. season|2016\u201317]]<ref name=sb1617>{{soccerbase season|31018|2016|accessdate=16 July 2017}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|30||1||3||1||1||0||colspan=2|\u2014||34||2\n|-\n|[[2017\u201318 Middlesbrough F.C. season|2017\u201318]]<ref name=sb1718>{{soccerbase season|31018|2017|accessdate=6 August 2018}}</ref>\n|Championship\n|40||3||2||0||3||0||2{{efn|Appearances in [[EFL Championship play-offs|Championship play-offs]]}}||0||47||3\n|-\n|[[2018\u201319 Middlesbrough F.C. season|2018\u201319]]<ref name=sb1819>{{soccerbase season|31018|2018|accessdate=21 June 2019}}</ref>\n|Championship\n|38||2||1||0||1||0||colspan=2|\u2014||40||2\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!153||9||6||1||9||0||2||0||170||10\n|-\n|[[Blackburn Rovers F.C.|Blackburn Rovers]]\n|[[2019\u201320 Blackburn Rovers F.C. season|2019\u201320]]<ref name=sb1920>{{soccerbase season|31018|2019|accessdate=21 June 2019}}</ref>\n|Championship\n|19||1||0||0||1||1||colspan=2|\u2014||20||2\n|-\n!colspan=3|Career total\n!558||49||55||6||35||4||33||3||681||62\n|}\n\n{{notelist}}\n\n===International===\n{{updated|match played 18 November 2014}}<ref>{{NFT player |id=9996 |name=Downing, Stewart |accessdate=21 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=wikitable style=text-align:center\n|+ Appearances and goals by national team and year\n|-\n!National team!!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=8|[[England national football team|England]]\n|2005||1||0\n|-\n|2006||8||0\n|-\n|2007||7||0\n|-\n|2008||5||0\n|-\n|2009||2||0\n|-\n|2011||9||0\n|-\n|2012||2||0\n|-\n|2014||1||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total||35||0\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Middlesbrough'''\n*[[Football League Cup]]: [[2003\u201304 Football League Cup|2003\u201304]]<ref name=2004LC/>\n*[[UEFA Cup]] runner-up: [[2005\u201306 UEFA Cup|2005\u201306]]<ref name=2006UC/>\n*[[Football League Championship]] runner-up: [[2015\u201316 Football League Championship|2015\u201316]]<ref>{{cite book |editor-first=John |editor-last=Anderson |title=Sky Sports Football Yearbook 2016\u20132017 |year=2016 |publisher=Headline Publishing Group |location=London |isbn=978-1-4722-3395-0 |pages=234\u2013235}}</ref>\n\n'''Aston Villa'''\n*Football League Cup runner-up: [[2009\u201310 Football League Cup|2009\u201310]]<ref>{{cite news |first=Phil |last=McNulty |title=Aston Villa 1\u20132 Man Utd |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/league_cup/8531179.stm |website=BBC Sport |date=28 February 2010 |accessdate=7 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n'''Liverpool'''\n*Football League Cup: [[2011\u201312 Football League Cup|2011\u201312]]<ref>{{cite news |first=Chris |last=Bevan |title=Cardiff 2\u20132 Liverpool |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/17093419 |website=BBC Sport |date=26 February 2012 |accessdate=21 September 2016}}</ref>\n*[[FA Cup]] runner-up: [[2011\u201312 FA Cup|2011\u201312]]<ref>{{cite news |first=Phil |last=McNulty |title=Chelsea 2\u20131 Liverpool |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/17878435 |website=BBC Sport |date=5 May 2012 |accessdate=7 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n'''Individual'''\n*[[Alan Hardaker Trophy]]: [[2012 Football League Cup Final|2012]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Alan Hardaker Trophy winners |url=http://origin-www.football-league.co.uk/page/AlanHardakerTrophyWinners/0,,10794~1354852,00.html |publisher=The Football League |date=24 February 2003 |accessdate=21 September 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] Player of the Season: [[2010\u201311 Aston Villa F.C. season|2010\u201311]]<ref>{{cite news |first=Mat |last=Kendrick |title=Aston Villa: Stewart Downing happy to stay on at 'fantastic club' |url=http://www.birminghammail.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/aston-villa-stewart-downing-happy-154215 |newspaper=Birmingham Mail |date=11 May 2011 |accessdate=7 December 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Middlesbrough F.C. Player of the Year|Middlesbrough Player of the Year]]: [[2004\u201305 Middlesbrough F.C. season|2004\u201305]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Downing nets yet another top title |url=http://www.gazettelive.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/downing-nets-yet-another-top-3798490 |newspaper=Teesside Gazette |location=Middlesbrough |date=17 May 2005 |accessdate=7 December 2017}}</ref>\n*Middlesbrough Young Player of the Year: [[2003\u201304 Middlesbrough F.C. season|2003\u201304]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Boateng beats pain |url=http://www.gazettelive.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/boateng-beats-pain-3828722 |newspaper=Teesside Gazette |location=Middlesbrough |date=6 May 2004 |accessdate=7 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*[https://www.rovers.co.uk/teams/first-team/midfielder/stewart-downing/ Profile] at the Blackburn Rovers F.C. website\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Awards\n| bg = gold\n| fg = navy\n| list1 = \n{{Alan Hardaker Trophy}}