=Millennium Volunteers, Youth Volunteers, Volunteering Opportunities |publisher=Bacyp.co.uk |accessdate=21 October 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091207113727/http://www.bacyp.co.uk/action.htm |archivedate=7 December 2009}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"look\">{{citation |journal=[[Look (UK magazine)|Look magazine]] |title=Interview: Jameela Jamil |publisher=IPC Group Limited |location=London, UK |date=16 February 2010}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"fas\">{{Dead link|date=December 2010}}{{cite web |url=http://www.premiermodelstyle.com/beta/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=92&Itemid=62 |title=Jameela Jamil |publisher=Premiermodelstyle.com |accessdate=21 October 2010}}{{dead link|date=November 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"orange\">{{cite web |url=http://www.channel4.com/programmes/orange-rockcorps/episode-guide/series-1/episode-7 |title=Orange RockCorps \u2013 Series 1 \u2013 Episode 7 \u2013 Orange Rockcorps 2009 |publisher=Channel 4 |date=19 September 2009 |accessdate=21 October 2010}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"vim\">{{cite web |url=http://nationalawards.vinspired.com/show.html |title=national awards |publisher=Nationalawards.vinspired.com |accessdate=21 October 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100105030436/http://nationalawards.vinspired.com/show.html |archivedate=5 January 2010}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"sponge\">{{cite web |url=http://www.popsugar.co.uk/Photos-from-Spongebob-Squarepants-Tenth-Birthday-Celebration-Charity-Auction-Saturdays-Sophie-Ellis-Bextor-7132015 |title=Photos from the Spongebob Squarepants Tenth Birthday Celebration and Charity Auction With The Saturdays, Sophie Ellis-Bextor |publisher=Popsugar.co.uk |date=22 January 2010 |accessdate=21 October 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110725154340/http://www.popsugar.co.uk/Photos-from-Spongebob-Squarepants-Tenth-Birthday-Celebration-Charity-Auction-Saturdays-Sophie-Ellis-Bextor-7132015 |archivedate=25 July 2011}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"nylon\">{{cite journal |journal=[[Nylon (magazine)|Nylon]] |publisher=Nylon Holding Inc. |location=New York |date=December 2009 |first1=Katie |last1=Mulloy |author2=Bella Howard (photographer) |author3=Steve Morriss (stylist)}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite journal |journal=[[Vogue (British magazine)|Vogue]] |title=British Editorial Class of 2010 |date=January 2010}}\n* {{cite news |agency=Press Association |url=http://www.tv.com/jameela-jamil-finds-t4-surreal/story/17210.html |title=Jameela Jamil finds T4 surreal |work=TV.com |date=11 August 2009 |accessdate=21 October 2010}}\n* {{cite web |url=http://www.nowmagazine.co.uk/celebrity-news/tv-news/435736/t4-s-jameela-jamil-i-was-stuck-in-portaloo-for-over-an-hour/1 |title=T4 presenter Jameela Jamil: I was stuck in Portaloo for over an hour |work=Now Magazine |first=Lorraine |last=Crowther |date=24 December 2009 |accessdate=21 October 2010}}\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oXsLPgAOmyg Jameela explains how she got her first DJ gig, Elton John's birthday party, on Conan] Conan. 5 December 2019. \n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{IMDb name}}\n* {{twitter}}\n* {{instagram}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-media}}\n{{Succession box\n| before = [[Scott Mills]]\n| title = [[BBC Radio 1]]<br>Chart show presenter\n| years = 13 January 2013 \u2013 18 January 2015\n| after = [[Clara Amfo]]\n}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jamil, Jameela}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:British people of Pakistani descent]]\n[[Category:English people of Indian descent]]\n[[Category:English television actresses]]\n[[Category:British actresses of Indian descent]]\n[[Category:English television presenters]]\n[[Category:English female models]]\n[[Category:English feminists]]\n[[Category:BBC Radio 1 presenters]]\n[[Category:Actresses from London]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century English actresses]]\n[[Category:English people of Pakistani descent]]\n[[Category:BBC 100 Women]]\n[[Category:Women radio presenters]]\n[[Category:English game show hosts]]\n[[Category:Queer actors]]\n[[Category:Queer women]]\n[[Category:LGBT entertainers from England]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|English actress and radio presenter}}\n{{Use British English|date=February 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Jameela Jamil\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image              = Jameela Jamil at the 2018 Comic-Con International (42913091955) (cropped).jpg\n| alt                = Jamil smiles with a black microphone in front of her\n| caption            = Jamil at the 2018 [[San Diego Comic-Con]]\n| birth_name         = Jameela Alia Burton-Jamil\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1986|2|25}}\n| birth_place        = [[Hampstead, London]], England\n| occupation         = {{Flatlist|\n* Presenter\n* actress\n* DJ\n}}\n| years_active       = 2009\u2013present\n| partner            = [[James Blake (musician)|James Blake]] (2015\u2013present)\n| website            = {{Official URL}}\n}}\n\n'''Jameela Alia Burton-Jamil'''<ref name=tvg>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/jameela-jamil/credits/919039/|title=Jameela Jamil Biography|magazine=[[TV Guide]]|accessdate=9 January 2020|archivedate=9 January 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20200109201609/https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/jameela-jamil/bio/919039/|url-status=live|date=}}</ref>(Born February 25, 1986)<ref>{{cite web |title=Jameela Jamil Archives |url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrities/jameela-jamil/ |website=Us Weekly |accessdate=20 January 2020}}</ref> is an English actress, radio presenter, model, writer and activist. She began her career on [[T4 (Channel 4)|T4]], where she hosted a pop culture series from 2009 until 2012. She then became the radio host of ''[[The Official Chart]]'', and was co-host of ''[[The Official Chart#The Official Chart Update|The Official Chart Update]]'' alongside [[Scott Mills]] on [[BBC Radio 1]]. She was the first solo female presenter of the BBC Radio 1 chart show.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/article/30474721/clara-amfo-to-present-bbc-radio-1s-official-chart-show |title=Clara Amfo to present BBC Radio 1's ''Official Chart Show'' |access-date=30 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nFollowing a breast cancer scare in 2016, Jamil moved to the United States. Whilst there, she was cast as Tahani Al-Jamil in the [[NBC]] fantasy comedy series ''[[The Good Place]]''.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url= http://deadline.com/2016/02/good-place-jameela-jamil-cast-mike-schur-nbc-series-1201709616/ |title=''Good Place'': English presenter Jameela Jamil cast in Mike Schur NBC series |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |date=26 February 2016 |magazine=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date=30 January 2017}}</ref> She has modelled for both [[British Vogue|British]] and ''[[Vogue (magazine)|American Vogue]]'', ''[[Glamour (magazine)|Glamour]]'', ''[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]'', and ''[[Teen Vogue]]'', and has written for ''[[The Times]]'', ''Cosmopolitan'', ''[[The Huffington Post]]'', and ''[[Company (magazine)|Company]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jameelajamil.co.uk/about|title=About|last=Jamil|first=Jameela|publisher=Jameela Jamil official website|access-date=2019-11-14}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nJamil was born in [[Hampstead, London]], England, United Kingdom, to a [[Muslims in India|Muslim Indian]] father and a [[Muslims in Pakistan|Muslim Pakistani]] mother.<ref name=telegraph21May2018>{{cite newspaper|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/tv/2018/05/21/good-place-star-jameela-jamil-told-old-ethnic-fat-us/|title=The Good Place star Jameela Jamil told she was 'too old, too ethnic and too fat' for the US|first=Zoah|last=Hedges-Stocks|newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|location=UK|date=21 May 2018|accessdate=9 January 2020|archivedate= 9 September 2019|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20190909202046/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/tv/2018/05/21/good-place-star-jameela-jamil-told-old-ethnic-fat-us/|url-status=live}}</ref> She was born with congenital hearing loss and [[labyrinthitis]], which she has had several operations to correct. She stated in 2015 that she had 70% audibility in her left ear and 50% in her right ear.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-news/jameela-jamil-faced-cancer-spine-5555978 |title=Jameela Jamil has faced cancer and spine damage but has never felt better |last=McGrath |first=Nick |date=20 April 2015 |work=Mirror |access-date=10 April 2018}}</ref> Jamil says she was \"bookish and shy\" at school.<ref name=\"met\" /> At the age of nine, she was diagnosed with hypermobile [[Ehlers\u2013Danlos syndromes|Ehlers-Danlos syndrome]], a genetic disorder affecting the connective tissue in the body. It can cause a very wide variety of symptoms, some of which can be life threatening. The most common symptoms include hypermobile [[joint]]s, joint pain, stretchy skin, abnormal [[scar]] formation, extreme fatigue, digestive problems and heart issues.<ref name=\"instagram_B0q4jt7lEAj\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B0q4jt7lEAj/ |title=Jameela Jamil on Instagram: \"Proud to be an @ehlers.danlos advocate of the year. I got diagnosed at 9 years old and there is still so little information 20 years later\u2026\" |website=Instagram|access-date=5 October 2019}}</ref> As a teenager, she suffered from [[anorexia nervosa]] and did not eat a full meal between the ages of 14 and 17. She has stated that she believes her eating disorder developed due to societal pressure:\n\n{{quote|I was bombarded with a narrative that had no alternative. There were never any women who were celebrated for their intellect ... and all of my magazines were selling me weight loss products or telling me to be thin. Otherwise, I wasn't worth anything.<ref name=\":3\">{{cite web |publisher=Channel 4 News |title=Jameela Jamil on banning airbrushing, the Kardashians and her traumatic teens |date=29 August 2018 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BXzO0z6fmhI |access-date=31 August 2018 |via=YouTube}}</ref>}}\n\nAt the age of 17, Jamil was struck by a car while running from a bee, breaking several bones and damaging her spine. She was told that she might never walk again, but she slowly recovered after [[steroid]] treatment and [[physiotherapy]], using a [[Zimmer frame]] to start walking.<ref name=\"nylon\" /><ref name=\"look\" /> She cites the car accident as what pushed her towards recovery, stating that it changed her relationship with her body and figuratively \"knocked some sense\" into her.<ref name=\":3\" /> She attended [[Queen's College, London|Queen's College]] School in London and taught English to foreign students at the Callan School of English in London.<ref name=\"look\" /> She also worked as a model, photographer, and fashion scout for Premier Model Management Limited.<ref name=\"nylon\" /><ref name=\"sky\" /><ref name=\"fas\" />\n\n==Career==\n===2009\u20132015: Early media career===\n[[File:Jameela jamil.jpg|right|thumb|Jamil, pictured at the [[London Fashion Week]], 2009]]\nJamil appeared on the [[E4 (channel)|E4]] show ''Music Zone'' towards the end of 2008. She began presenting T4 in 2009.<ref name=\"spec\" /><ref name=\"hack\" /> In January 2009, [[Alexa Chung]] left the morning TV show ''[[Freshly Squeezed]]''; Jamil succeeded her as co-host, alongside [[Nick Grimshaw]].<ref name=\"sky\" /><ref name=\"spec\" /><ref name=\"agy\" /><ref name=\"ds1\" />\n\nJamil presented ''The Closet'', an online fashion advice show on the social networking site [[Bebo]].<ref name=\"hack\" /><ref name=\"agy\" /><ref name=\"beb\" /> Created and produced by [[Twenty Twenty|Twenty Twenty Television]], it formed part of the ''Bebo Originals'' commission programme.<ref name=\"beb\" /> Jamil was photographed for a ''[[Vogue (British magazine)|Vogue]]'' feature on \"British Editorial Class of 2010\" in January of that year, by [[David Bailey (photographer)|David Bailey]].\n\nFrom 2011 to 2014 she wrote a column for ''[[Company (magazine)|Company]]'', the women's monthly magazine.<ref name=\"hack\" /><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://heavy.com/entertainment/2017/09/jameela-jamil-tahani-al-the-good-place-age-boyfriend-cast/ |title=Jameela Jamil as Tahani Al-Jamil: 5 Fast Facts You Need to Know |last=Levine |first=Daniel S. |date=20 September 2017 |work=Heavy.com |access-date=21 January 2018}}</ref> In January 2012, Jamil replaced [[June Sarpong]] as the new host of the reality show ''[[Playing It Straight#Channel 4|Playing It Straight]].''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/news/a344163/playing-it-straight-to-return-to-e4.html |title='Playing It Straight' to return to E4 |publisher=Digital Spy |date=6 October 2011 |accessdate=4 June 2012}}</ref> In 2012, it was announced that [[Reggie Yates]] would leave [[BBC Radio 1]] and Jamil would replace him. At the end of 2012 Jamil became the radio host of ''[[The Official Chart]]'', and was co-host of ''[[The Official Chart#The Official Chart Update|The Official Chart Update]]'' alongside [[Scott Mills]] on [[BBC Radio 1]]. Jamil made radio history, becoming the first sole female presenter of the BBC Radio 1 ''Chart'' ''show.''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/media/news/a436939/reggie-yates-vernon-kay-to-leave-radio-1-jameela-jamil-for-chart-show.html |title=Reggie Yates, Vernon Kay to leave Radio 1, Jameela Jamil for Chart Show |publisher=Digital Spy |date=9 November 2012 |accessdate=6 September 2013}}</ref> In June 2012, Jamil collaborated with [[Very (online retailer)|Very]] to debut her first fashion collection.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.very.co.uk/2012/06/the-exclusive-first-collection-designed-by-jameela-jamil-for-very-co-uk|title=The exclusive first collection designed by Jameela Jamil for Very.co.uk|date=21 June 2012|publisher=Blog.very.co.uk|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120903143557/http://blog.very.co.uk/2012/06/the-exclusive-first-collection-designed-by-jameela-jamil-for-very-co-uk/|archive-date=3 September 2012|accessdate=8 October 2012}}</ref>\n\n===2016\u2013present: Transition into acting===\n{{Quote box\n| quote = It's very exciting. I know it shouldn't be a big deal, but there's also a huge lack of ethnic minorities in showbiz. I'm completely Asian \u2013 not mix \u2013 and I'm so proud to be such a big part of Radio 1. I actually can't wait to get started now!\n| source = &nbsp;\u2014 {{small|Jamil, on being the first female host of ''[[The Official Chart]]''<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/music/radio/a450112/jameela-jamil-talks-radio-1-chart-show-its-just-like-football/ |title=Jameela Jamil talks Radio 1 Chart Show |first=Robert |last=Copsey |date=11 January 2013 |website=Digital Spy}}</ref>}}\n| quoted = true\n| bgcolor = #fafafa\n| align = right\n| width = 26%\n| border = 1px\n| fontsize = 88%\n}}\n\nFollowing a breast cancer scare, Jamil left London and moved to Los Angeles,<ref name=\"Elle\">{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.elle.com/culture/movies-tv/a23289305/jameela-jamil-the-good-place/ |title=Jameela Jamil Is on a 'Burger-Friendly, Life-Positive' Mission |last=Chocano |first=Carina |date=18 September 2018 |magazine=[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]|access-date=13 January 2019}}</ref> with no plans of acting, instead intending to work as a screenwriter.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wmagazine.com/story/jameela-jamil-the-good-place-hollywood-interview|title=Jameela Jamil Never Expected to Be An Actress\u2014Now, She's Fighting for Inclusivity|last=Hirschberg|first=Lynn|website=W Magazine|language=en|access-date=2019-11-23}}</ref> Her agent told her that [[Michael Schur]], who co-created ''[[Parks and Recreation]]'', was looking for a British actress for a new upcoming comedy series. Although Jamil had no prior acting experience at this point and was wary of auditioning, she agreed to do so. She was later recalled for a second interview, and was given the role.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-41609603 |title=Why Jameela Jamil is in a Good Place |first=Lauren |last=Turner |date=14 October 2017 |accessdate=9 November 2018 |work=BBC News}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.gq.com/story/jameela-jamil-the-good-place-interview |title=Jameela Jamil Had Never Acted Before 'The Good Place' |last=Fetters |first=Ashley |date=11 January 2018 |work=[[GQ]] |access-date=30 January 2018}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.avclub.com/jameela-jamil-suggests-you-take-all-your-good-place-spo-1821504551 |title=Jameela Jamil suggests you take all your Good Place spoiler requests to Ted \"Loose Lips\" Danson |last=Adams |first=Erik |date=4 January 2018 |work=[[The A.V. Club]] |access-date=30 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe show premiered in September 2016, with Jamil being a regular cast member of the [[NBC]] fantasy comedy series ''[[The Good Place]]'', where she plays Tahani Al-Jamil, (lit. 'Congratulations Beautiful' in [[Arabic language|Arabic]]), alongside [[Kristen Bell]], [[Ted Danson]] and [[William Jackson Harper]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2016/02/good-place-jameela-jamil-cast-mike-schur-nbc-series-1201709616/ |title='Good Place': British Presenter Jameela Jamil Cast In Mike Schur NBC Series |first=Nellie |last=Andreeva |date=25 February 2016 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=12 March 2016}}</ref> Jamil's character became known for her tendency to [[name drop]].<ref name=\"Deadline-Jamil\">{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2016/02/good-place-jameela-jamil-cast-mike-schur-nbc-series-1201709616/ |title='Good Place': British Presenter Jameela Jamil Cast in Mike Schur NBC Series |first=Nellie |last=Andreeva |date=25 February 2016 |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=12 March 2016}}</ref>\n\nJamil made her first American magazine cover on the February 2018 edition of ''The Cut''.<ref>{{Cite tweet |user=jameelajamil |first=Jameela |last=Jamil |number=960553609082687488 |title=My first USA cover! Thanks @thecut What a bloody lovely surprise that was. Interview is out now! https://www.instagram.com/p/Be0nENSFcbp/ |date=5 February 2018 |access-date=10 April 2018}}</ref> She provided her voice as a guest on the animated television series ''[[DuckTales (2017 TV series)|DuckTales]]''.<ref name=\"Jameela Jamil on Twitter\">{{cite tweet |user=jameelajamil |number=1043183443356540929 |title=Joining the cast of Ducktales and living out my childhood dream! couldn't be more excited. \ud83e\udd13 |date=21 September 2018 |first=Jameela |last=Jamil |accessdate=9 November 2018}}</ref> In 2018, Jamil joined the cast of Disney's Indian-inspired cartoon set in fictional Jalpur. ''Mira, Royal Detective'' is expected to air on Disney Junior channels in 2020, with Jamil playing Mira's Auntie Pushpa.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-46398137 |title=Jameela Jamil joins Disney Indian-inspired cartoon |date=30 November 2018 |work=BBC News}}</ref> In 2018, Jamil hosted a recurring segment on ''[[Last Call with Carson Daly]]'' during its final season, entitled \"Wide Awake with Jameela Jamil\".<ref>{{Citation|title=Last Call with Carson Daly|date=2019-11-22|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Last_Call_with_Carson_Daly&oldid=927451237|work=Wikipedia|language=en|access-date=2019-11-23}}</ref>\n\nSince 2019, Jamil has been the host of ''[[The Misery Index (TV series)|The Misery Index]]'', a comedy game show on [[TBS (American TV channel)|TBS]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Darwish |first1=Meaghan |title='The Misery Index' Unveils Premiere Date & First-Squirm Inducing Trailer (VIDEO) |url=https://www.tvinsider.com/795332/the-misery-index-tbs-impractical-jokers-comic-con-jameela-jamil-premiere-trailer/ |website=TV Insider |publisher=NTVB Media, Inc. |accessdate=20 December 2019 |date=18 July 2019}}</ref> \n\nIn March 2020, she posed fully-clothed in suit and tie for a [[Playboy]] magazine risqu\u00e9 for its \"On Speech\" issue. She later tweeted, \"From my Playboy shoot, I wanted to be shot like a man, No retouching, hi res, loose, comfortable clothes and completely unsexualized. I felt extremely free.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/tv/celebrity/jameela-jamil-poses-fully-clothed-in-suit-and-tie-in-playboy/ar-BB116Wut#image=BBUPCH9%7C4|title=Jameela Jamil poses fully-clothed in suit and tie in Playboy|website=www.msn.com|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pagesix.com/2020/03/12/jameela-jamil-poses-in-suit-and-tie-for-playboy-i-wanted-to-be-shot-like-a-man/|title=Jameela Jamil poses in suit and tie for Playboy: \u2018I wanted to be shot like a man\u2019|last=Fishman|first=Elana|date=2020-03-12|website=Page Six|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref>\n\n===Activism===\nLate in 2015, Jamil launched ''Why Not People?,'' an events and membership company dedicated to hosting live entertainment events accessible to people with disabilities.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/jameela-jamil-britain-deals-with-disability-by-pretending-its-not-happening-10341941.html |title=Jameela Jamil: 'Britain deals with disability by pretending it's not happening' |date=24 June 2015 |work=The Independent |access-date=10 April 2018}}</ref> In March 2018, Jamil created an [[Instagram]] account called I Weigh,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/i_weigh/ |title=I Weigh (@i_weigh) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos |website=www.instagram.com |access-date=7 June 2018}}</ref> inspired by a picture that she came across online of [[Kourtney Kardashian|Kourtney]], [[Kim Kardashian|Kim]] and [[Khlo\u00e9 Kardashian]] with their half-sisters [[Kendall Jenner|Kendall]] and [[Kylie Jenner]], detailing each woman's weight.<ref name=\"Jamil\">{{Cite news |url=http://jameelajamil.co.uk/post/171287759245/i-weigh |title=I weigh |last=Jamil |first=Jameela |work=Jameela Jamil \u2013 Diary of a Goon |access-date=7 June 2018}}</ref> Jamil describes I Weigh as \"a movement... for us to feel valuable and see how amazing we are, and look past the flesh on our bones\".<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/stories/highlights/17882788429217768/ |title=What is i_weigh \u2013 @i_weigh |website=www.instagram.com |access-date=7 June 2018}}</ref> The account welcomes submissions of followers' non-edited or airbrushed selfies using the hashtag #iweigh, with text describing the things that they feel grateful for or proud of.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\"Jamil\" /> In part due to this work, Jamil was listed as one of [[100 Women (BBC)|BBC's 100 Women]] during 2018.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-46225037 |title=BBC 100 Women 2018: Who is on the list? |date=19 November 2018 |work=BBC News |access-date=21 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nJamil has been a critic of diet shakes and eating suppressant products. She explained that as a teenager she starved herself, took laxatives and tips from celebrities on how to maintain a low weight. She has criticised rapper [[Cardi B]], [[the Kardashians]] and other influencers for promoting diet suppressants via social media.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bravotv.com/the-feast/cardi-b-diet-detox-tea-twitter-war-with-good-place-actress-jameela-jamil |title=Let's Break Down Cardi B's Expletive-Filled Twitter War Over \"Nonsense\" Detox Tea |date=28 November 2018 |website=Bravo TV Official Site}}</ref> Jamil created a petition via change.org, titled \"Stop celebrities promoting toxic diet products on social media\", with a goal of reaching 150,000 signatures. She called upon social media services such as [[Facebook]], [[Twitter]], and [[Instagram]] to ban the practice, noting its dangerous rhetoric on young impressionable teenagers.<ref name=\"pedestrian.tv\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.pedestrian.tv/health/jameela-jamil-petition-celeb-endorsed-diets/ |title=100,000 People Sign Jameela Jamil's Petition To Stop Celeb Endorsed Diets |date=10 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n{{Quote|quote=There's little to no information about the side effects or main ingredients, the harm they may cause or any of the science behind how these products are supposed to work. They are instead, flogged in glossy paid adverts by celebrities and influencers with no expertise or authority in nutrition/medicine/biology. |source =An excerpt from Jamil's diet petition<ref name=\"pedestrian.tv\" />|sign=}}\n\nJamil also supports the climate change movement, expressing her admiration for [[Jane Fonda]], [[Greta Thunberg]] and several other climate change activists. She stated that she herself does not want to get arrested for the cause, because of her brown female immigrant status.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://twitter.com/jameelajamil/status/1198651549737598976 |title=I think what Jane Fonda is doing for climate change awareness is so amazing. But people keep swarming me with messages asking me when I'm going to go and get arrested too. I am a brown female immigrant. I'm gonna support from the outside. And That is that on that. \u2764\ufe0f |date=24 November 2019 |website=Twitter}}</ref>\n\n===Charity===\nJamil appeared on C4 ''Orange Rockcorps 2009'', volunteering to help create a concert to fund local community projects.<ref name=\"orange\" /> She has supported the Cultural Learning Alliance, which promotes access to culture for children and young people,<ref name=\"spaghetti\" /> and Vinspired National Awards for people aged 16\u201325 who have contributed to their communities through volunteering.<ref name=\"bap\" /><ref name=\"vim\" /> Jamil designed her own version of [[SpongeBob SquarePants (character)|SpongeBob SquarePants]] to be auctioned off with all the proceeds going to Childline.<ref name=\"sponge\" />\nJamil also said that she would wear a chicken costume for the same number of days equal to the number of thousands of pounds she raises for [[Comic Relief]]. She was sponsored approximately \u00a316,000 and wore the costume for 16 consecutive days.<ref>{{cite web |last=Digital Spy |title=Jameela Jamil offers to wear chicken suit for a month for Comic Relief |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/showbiz/news/a461075/jameela-jamil-offers-to-wear-chicken-suit-for-a-month-for-comic-relief.html |accessdate=17 March 2013|date=23 February 2013 }}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\nJamil was one of fifteen women selected to appear on the cover of the September 2019 issue of [[British Vogue|British ''Vogue'']] \"Forces for Change\", by guest editor [[Meghan, Duchess of Sussex]].<ref name=\"IT-2019-07-31\">{{cite web |title=Meghan Markle puts Sin\u00e9ad Burke on the cover of Vogue's September issue |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/life-and-style/fashion/meghan-markle-puts-sin\u00e9ad-burke-on-the-cover-of-vogue-s-september-issue-1.3970604 |website=The Irish Times |accessdate=31 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 August 2019, Jamil was awarded \"Advocate of the Year\" from the [[Ehlers-Danlos Society]].<ref name=\"instagram_B0q4jt7lEAj\"/>\n\n==Personal life==\nJamil has been in a relationship with musician [[James Blake (musician)|James Blake]] since 2015.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BhKOtyql79f/ |title=Jameela Jamil on Instagram: \"3 years with this untalented bastard \u2764\ufe0f\" |access-date=7 June 2018}} \u2013 va [[Instagram]]</ref> She is openly [[queer]].<ref>{{cite tweet |user=jameelajamil |number= 1225165342965669888 |title= Twitter is Brutal |last=Jamil &nbsp;\ud83c\udf08 |first=Jameela |date= 5 February 2020 |accessdate= 6 February 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-51399416|title=Jameela Jamil announces she is \u2018queer\u2019 after backlash over TV role|publisher=[[British Broadcasting Corporation]]/[[BBC News]]|date=6 February 2020|accessdate=6 February 2020|last=Hunte|first=Ben}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/insider/alist/jameela-jamil-comes-out-queer-legendary-judge-backlash-a4354926.html|title=Jameela Jamil comes out as queer on Twitter after backlash over Legendary judge role|publisher=[[Evening Standard]]|date=6 February 2020|accessdate=6 February 2020|last=Abrams|first=Margaret}}</ref>\n\nOn the 1 October 2018 episode of ''[[Good Morning America]]''{{snd}}complete with video footage<ref>{{cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Rn8kXmZPXq8&t=11s |people=[[Olly Murs]], Jameela Jamil |title=Olly Murs - Challenge 1 (Orange RockCorps) |medium=[[YouTube]] |location=[[London]] |date=15 August 2011 |access-date=31 January 2020 }}</ref>{{snd}}Jamil revealed that she lost a tooth, smashed her nose, broke her elbow and got a concussion when she slipped and fell on her face while running around the set with [[Olly Murs]] at a recorded event leading up to the pair acting as [[Master of ceremonies|presenters]] at the [[Rockcorps|Orange Rockcorps]] volunteer's London concert of September 2010.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.goodmorningamerica.com/news/video/good-place-star-jameela-jamil-reveals-lost-tooth-58210186 |title= 'The Good Place' star Jameela Jamil reveals how she lost her tooth in on-set fall |publisher=[[ABC News]] |date=1 October 2018 |access-date= 31 January 2020 }}</ref>\n\nIn May 2019, Jamil shared that she had an abortion earlier in her life. She stated, \"It was the best decision I have ever made. Both for me, and for the baby I didn't want, and wasn't ready for, emotionally, psychologically and financially.\"<ref>{{Cite tweet |user=jameelajamil |number=1128013071295762432 |title=I had an abortion when I was young, and it was the best decision I have ever made. Both for me, and for the baby I didn't want, and wasn't ready for, emotionally, psychologically and financially. So many children will end up in foster homes. So many lives ruined. So very cruel. |access-date=16 May 2019 |date=13 May 2019 |first=Jameela |last=Jamil}}</ref>\n\nOn 3 October 2019 in interview on [[Hard Talk]] a [[BBC News Channel]] programme she revealed that she had been raped several times in her life and in the past she looked at blaming women but has changed to blaming the societal patriarchy that produces that scenario.<ref>{{https://www.bbc.co.uk/iplayer/episode/m000920z/hardtalk-jameela-jamil-actor-and-activist}}</ref>\n\nOn 10 October 2019, as part of [[World Mental Health Day]], Jamil revealed she survived a suicide attempt six years prior. She criticised the lack of services for those who struggled with mental health issues. She also revealed that she partook in [[EMDR|EMDR therapy]] to treat her [[PTSD|post traumatic stress disorder]]<ref>{{Cite tweet |user=jameelajamil |number=1182317661989961730 |title=Today is #WorldMentalHealthDay This month, 6 years ago, I tried to take my own life. I'm so lucky that I survived, and went on to use EMDR to treat my severe PTSD. I urge you to hang on just a bit longer and ask for help if you need it. Because things can turn around. I promise. |last=Jamil &nbsp;\ud83c\udf08 |first=Jameela |date=10 October 2019|access-date=10 October 2019}}</ref> as a result of being bed bound for a year after the car accident when she was 17, being raped and having a nervous breakdown in her early 20s.<ref> [https://www.msn.com/en-nz/entertainment/celebrity/jameela-jamils-severe-ptsd/ar-AAFFa9S Jameela Jamil's severe PTSD], MSN, 11 August 2019\n</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2019 || ''[[How to Build a Girl]]'' ||  ||\n|-\n| 2020 || ''[[Marry Me (upcoming film)|Marry Me]]'' || ||\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2009\u20132012 ||''[[Freshly Squeezed]]'' || Herself || Lead host\n|-\n| 2012 || ''[[Playing It Straight]]'' || Herself || Host\n|-\n| 2014 || ''[[Celebrity Juice]]'' || Herself || Series 11, episode 8<ref>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Celebrity_Juice_episodes Retrieved March 20, 2020</ref>\n|-\n| 2015 || 